Why DevOps?
Before we know what DevOps is, it is extremely important to understand how DevOps came into existence. Before DevOps, we had the waterfall model and an agile model for software development. So letâ€™s have a look at the waterfall model.

Waterfall Model
The waterfall model can be defined as a sequential process in the development of a system or software that follows a top-down approach. This model was simple and linear. The Waterfall model had numerous stages such as Requirement Definition, Software Design, Implementation, Testing, Verification, and Maintenance.
